B. Adjustable Neighbor Discovery
We Ô¨Årst deÔ¨Åne the neighbor discovery problem as: Problem 1: Design the neighbor discovery schedule Si = {si(t)|t ‚â• 0} for node ui where:

si(t) =

0 if ui chooses state OF F 1 if ui chooses state ON

For two neighboring nodes ui and uj, denote the start time of ui and uj as Œ¥i and Œ¥j respectively, there exits T such that:

si(T ) = sj(T ) = 1

Notice that, the nodes can start asynchronously which

implies they could have different start time. In the problem

deÔ¨Ånition, node ui starts at time Œ¥i while uj starts at slot Œ¥j. The discovery latency between them (denoted as L(i, j)) is

deÔ¨Åned as:

